Hi, thanks for downloading this workflow alongside with my models.

First I highly recommend to download my enhancer.. It's working without it but you will get better results with it. You can download it from here: https://ko-fi.com/s/34e553e28c

I have tested it with following checkpoints: 
- Hephaistos NextGen Tensor V1.1 avaible on Tensor.art: https://tensor.art/models/697912008114231188
- Colossus Project V6 Exprimental 2 on civitai: https://civitai.com/models/147720/colossus-project-xl-sfwandnsfw


Here is a basic overview over this basic enhancer workflow:

CONDITIONING:

- This workflow has two different conditioning sytems.. you can toggle them with the two conditioning switches. sometimes its worth to toggle those

GROUP BYPASSER:

- You can use the fast group bypasser on the left; here you can enable or disable different things like Lora, deepshrink and the different stages. If you want bypass stage 2 you must also use the bypass stage 2 switch..
Also you can enable IMG to IMG

IMG to IMG:

To get this mode to work you have to do following steps:
- enable IMG to IMG on the bypasser. 
- set the CR img2img switch to img to img
- Disable Stage 1

Down below is the control for the IMG to IMG mode:


You can here enhance old AI images or whatever you want. you can even load image batches
make sure that your computer can handle the image size.. (for the best results the image should roughly has the same size as the normal input. Use the CR upscale image for up- or downscaling.

Sometimes you want add something to the image.. use that ksampler for that or just bypass it.
You can also bypass the second stage as I explained above.

Pro tricks:

- if you just simple want to enhance the image without adding something you can also switch the two text inputs of the third stage to 2. This can be also used to add something only for the third stage.
- on Stage 2 is a model switch. It allows to disable or enable the Lora for stage 2 set it to "1" if your Lora has negative effects on the image.

Have fun creating
